//////////
NPM > node package manager
/////

package.json
> Entry Point to app
> contains command like > start, test
> contains all package we use
> meta data (description, version ,name)

//////Step to generate package.json
** NodeJs must be install in system
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm init
> Answer all question
> type "yes"

//////Step to install package
** NodeJs must be install in system
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm i package-name

///es5
var a = 10
var b = "my age is "+a 
"my age is 10"

///Es6
var a = 10
var b = `my age is ${a}`

////////Global package////
Only Package that is require to 
run app (require before app start)
will go global

////////////
#window
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g packageName

#mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g packageName

//////////Nodemon////
> automatically restart the server when any change detected
> npm i -g nodemon

////////dev dependency/package////
> go inside the folder
> npm i packageName --save-dev